// Path Mapping:
// - File Server: G:\shared\clients\client 1\my doc.pdf
// - Root Path: G:\shared\clients
// - SharePoint Path (without SharePointBasePath): clients\client 1\my doc.pdf
// - SharePoint Path (with SharePointBasePath: "etc"): etc\clients\client 1\my doc.pdf
// The last folder name in FileServerPath ("clients") will be included in SharePoint paths
// SharePointBasePath (optional): Adds a prefix folder in SharePoint (e.g., "etc" creates "etc\clients\...")
//
// FolderNameTransform (optional): Transform folder names during migration
// Example: Simplify folder names by removing everything after the base name
//   "FolderNameTransform": {
//     "SimplifyFolders": true,
//     "NameMappings": {
//       "Clients": "clients"
//     }
//   }
// - SimplifyFolders: If true, removes everything after " (" or " -" from folder names
//   Example: "Clients (ETC - Wilco)" -> "Clients", "Projects - Old" -> "Projects"
// - NameMappings: Object mapping exact folder names to new names (applied after simplification)
//   Example: "Clients" -> "clients" (case normalization)
// - RemovePattern: Optional regex pattern for custom removal (advanced use)

